text: Corine Spier-Rottschäfer (8 May 1938 – 24 September 2020) was a Dutch model and beauty queen. She won the 1959 Miss World contest, representing the Netherlands.. missworld.com She was the first woman from her country to win the title. The pageant was held in London, United Kingdom. Rottschäfer was born in Hoorn, Netherlands. Rottschäfer died on 24 September 2020 at the age of 82.Eerste Nederlandse Miss World Corine Spier overleden ==References== Category:1938 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Dutch models Category:Miss World winners Category:People from North Holland
